Notes concernant printf

%i = integer
%c = char
%s = string
%p = pointeur
%u = unsigned int
%x ou %X = hexa en lower case ou upper
% = imprimer % (printf("%%"))

!integer!
%i takes integer value as integer value with decimal, hexadecimal or octal type.
To enter a value in hexadecimal format – value should be provided by preceding “0x” and 
value in octal format – value should be provided by preceding “0”.

for example : 

int x = 12 => printf("%i", x) = 12
int x = 012 => printf("%i", x) = 10
int x = 0x12 ou 0X12 => printf("%i", x) = 18

!Flags, width, period, precision!
toujours entre # et le type et dans l'ordre suivant
% | flags (- | 0) | width (*) | period (.) | argument type

